in orders placed before the opening of trade on the Tokyo Stock
Exchange after the Japanese clothing chain forecast a 17 percent
drop in full-year profit on slowing sales.  The shares were offered at 10,380 yen as of 8:05 a.m. local
time, blow their 12,390 yen close on Friday, Oct. 8. Japanese
markets were closed for a holiday on Monday.  After Fridayâ€™s close, the operator of the Uniqlo store
chain said net income for the 12 months ending in August would
